postcontent:
Be the envy of your shooting friends with the GSG 522 SD. This GSG MP5 22lr rifle has it all...the looks, accuracy, price and cool accessories. If you're looking for a great shooting tactical 22 rifle that doesn't look like an AR15, the GSG 522 is one of the best options for you. 

You can easily add on some of the fun GSG 522 accessories like a retractable stock, a nice BSA Red Dot or a 110 round drum magazine.

The 522 SD has a sling loop built into the left side of the standard stock and one on the trigger guard. The SD does not have a front sling loop like the 522 carbine does.

All versions of the GSG 522 has a tactical rail up top that allows you to easily mount red dots, reflex red dots or any size scope you'd like to put up there. The rail is built in so there is no added parts to buy.

The GSG 522 SD features a rubber ribbed hand guard and larger "SD" barrel shroud. The GSG 522 carbine features a more rigid plastic hand guard and smaller barrel shroud. You can easily remove the front hand guard for cleaning or to put on an after market front hand guard.

title: For Sale:  .50 cal BMG AR15 Upper by Watson's Weapons BIG BADDABOOM!
postcontent:
LOOK OUT-IT’S ANOTHER POLARBEAR6 SALE 
You think you got it all, huh? So you got the AR upper in .22? OK, that’s good for cheap plinking. So you got the AR upper in 9mm? OK, that’s fun at the range. So you got the AR upper in .300 or the Beowulf? OK, now your AR15 can punch above its weight. But if you want a black belt in AR15, you’re going to want this: 

UP FOR SALE: THIS AR15 .50BMG CALIBER UPPER BY WATSONS WEAPONS! 

Ladies and Gentlemen, submitted for your approval is this .50 caliber AR15 upper! This is NOT the Beowulf, but the honest-to-goodness .50BMG! This is the one you want to take your long-range shooting game to the next level. With this gun, you can measure your shots in terms of zip codes, not yards! You also turn your AR15 into a .50 cal rifle without buying another gun. Your wife will respect your cunning! (Now she certainly won’t be able to gripe about you buying another gun. If she asks, you just got some parts for the gun you already own-she can't hold THAT against you, right? Trust me-I’m married. Alternately, just tell her it’s some plumbing supplies for that household project…)

I picked up this beauty at The Armory in Virginia Beach in 2001. I’ve put approximately 25 rounds through her. I like owning a .50, but family, time, and a distinct lack of sufficient real estate for shooting In NOVA forces me to part with her. I’m hoping you can find her a good home with wide open spaces to put her through her paces. 

This monstrous beast was constructed by Watson’s Weapons of Mound, Minnesota. This upper measures approximately 36” long with a big, baffled muzzle break, bipod, heavy MG-style carry handle, flat top railed upper, bolt and bolt crank, and a big, padded carry bag/shooting mat. Sorry, no scope included with this auction, but let me warn you up front-you want to buy a quality scope for this rifle. If you try to go cheap, the .50 will eat your scope for breakfast.

This .50 cal upper is not a semi-auto Barrett Navy Seal Sniper Rifle. You will not be taking on the Taliban or ISIS or Cobra with this bad mother. It fires via a single shot crank-in bolt, so it's not a fast action and you won’t get a follow-up shot if you miss, but I assume you’re shooting this at stationary long-range targets, not invading North Koreans, UFOs, or game. (Shoot this at game and I think you’ll spend half the day looking for enough bits to fill a Ziploc bag.) It might be slow to load, but I guess it ensures there are no bolt failures with the .50 cartridge, and I’m fine with that. You will be able to take your target shooting game to the next level with this gun. 

Price: $1400. As always, I'm willing to entertain interesting offers, i.e. Indiana's Crystal Skull, phased plasma rifle in a 40 watt range, Hitler's Jockstrap, etc, but CASH IS KING. 

Condition: Used, Very Good. Approximately 25 rounds fired down the pipe. Some minor wear to finish. Comes with bolt, bolt crank, padded case, and big honking upper/sewer pipe. Reminds me of Oddball's Loudener (See Kelly's Heroes).

Terms: I prefer face2face transfers. I will travel to meet you within about 100 miles of Manassas. This is NOT a gun, so no credentials required. My time is money, so if you want to meet and refuse to buy, I request $20 for the trip. 
If you really want this upper and can not meet face2face, I can arrange shipping for an additional $80. Long-Distance purchasers shall complete payment for the full amount via Paypal prior to shipment. This upper is not for sale to Californians or residents of states where this item is illegal. Do your homework-I am not responsible for keeping you legal.

title: For Sale/Trade:  ugo Mauser 24/47 all matching with Royal Yugo and German markings
postcontent:
Up for sale is a Yugoslavian Mauser Model 24/47. This rifle is all matching numbers to include the receiver, barrel, stock, bolt and magazine (magazine is a forced match, the others are not).

This is not a Mitchell Mauser. It is import stamped.

Previous arsenal and manufacture markings were scrubbed on this one, but are still visible.
Faintly below the 24/47 markings Royal Yugo markings can be seen, as well as the location of original manufacture (Artillery Technical Institute). This makes original manufacture prewar (1928-31). Hard to get a picture of this as it is so faint, but it is there and I certainly welcome anyone to inspect it in person if they wish.

There are also two scrubbed German acceptance stamps, one on the receiver, indicating that the action (not the rifle as it sits today) was seized and put into German service, and one on the bolt release. So the action certainly saw combat during WWII.

The rifling is nearly flawless. The rifle does have some surface rust on the receiver, but this is limited and there is no corrosion. Not pretty but this rifle has been through a lot looking at the number/type of arsenal marks and stock markings.

Cycles great, shoots/groups dead on (though I don't have anywhere to shoot long range, so a little high at 100 yards as expected).

I have taken pictures of the rifle in and out, including all the markings should anyone wish to see more, ask questions etc.

All and all would make an all matching good shooter with a little bit of history behind it.

(Source for manufacture date/location)
http://candrsenal.com/rifle-serbian-mauser-model-1924/

title: For Sale/Trade:  FN FNX 45 Tactical FDE/TAN
postcontent:
I'm completely redoing this ad because I just assumed that anyone who would contact me would know exactly WHAT this pistol is and specifically be looking for this model. Apparently that was not the case because I've had people ask me if it comes with a threaded barrel. I've had people ask if it includes night sights. I've had people ask if it comes with the hard case or the soft case etc. Lets try this again! 

What I'm selling is the FN FNX-45 Tactical in FDE color.

The FNX-45 Tactical has an interesting history. In 2005, the US military launched the Joint Combat Pistol program (JCP) to find a replacement for the Beretta M9. The program was searching for a .45ACP caliber pistol with day/night sights, an integrated Picatinny rail and a threaded barrel for accepting suppressors. FN submitted the FNP-45-USG to those trials but the Military later suspended the program.

FN marketed a model of this gun called the FNP-45 Tactical but it had some issues so they later re-released the new FNX-45 Tactial. That it what I'm selling, the FNX-45 Tactical.

This gun includes Trijicon Night sights, raised for a silencer. This gun includes an extended, threaded barrel for usage with a silencer. This gun DOES come come in the TAN colored soft case that has pouches for the pistol, magazines, tools, accessories AND a silencer.

I have fired ONE box of .45ACP target ammo from this pistol, that is it. This pistol is like brand new in the case.

I paid $1199.99 for this pistol, PLUS 6% sales tax. The total was $1270.94 out the door. 

I would like to hopefully trade for an HK45CT. I would also maybe trade for an HK45C if it includes something to make the trade values the same.

That or I would sell this for the cash price of um, maybe $1000.00 dollars or so?

These guns are VERY rare right now. Not many people have them in-stock. If a store does not currently have one, they can NOT order them FNH is currently not shipping them. Most of of the major wholesalers are listing these as "hard to get" and out-of-stock w/ no ETA. I'm being told 4 to 6 months.

Feel free to call your local gun store and try to order one in FDE or there are some on Gunbroker.

- This feedback improves the user’s ability to “ride the reset” to improve follow up shot speed and placement.
- The trigger weight can be adjusted to as low as 3 lbs. A lighter pull weight requires less pressure, reducing trigger fatigue and improving accuracy.
- The pre-travel and over-travel are adjustable to allow for a shorter pull, crisper break and faster reset.
- Trigger adjustments will give the benefit of short take up, post break travel and will result in a a shorter reset.

title: For Sale:  NEW PSA 16" Upper in 5.56 w/ 1:7 Stainless Barrel
postcontent: Includes full auto BCG and charging handle.Once upon a time, a "dissipator" AR was created by taking a 20" rifle-length gas system upper and cutting the barrel down to 16". This allowed the shooter to keep the long sight radius of a rifle for accuracy, but keep the carbine length barrel for maneuverability. The proximity of the gas port to the muzzle, however, played havoc with timing and made reliability a hit or miss proposition. Advances in AR technology have produced reliable carbine and mid-length gas systems, that can be hidden using low-profile gas blocks. This allows for a front sight base to be pinned in the rifle position for the longer sight radius without the worry of the unorthodox gas port location affecting operation. We use the term "mock" to differentiate our dissipator from a cut-down rifle length version. Barrel: 416 Stainless steel. Chambered in 5.56 NATO, with a 1/7 twist, M4 barrel extension, and a mid-length gas system. Barrel is is finished off with a classic rifle-length handguard, F-Marked gas sight base, and A2 flash hider.Upper: Forged 7075-T6 A3 AR upper is made to MIL-SPECS and hard coat anodized black for durability. Featuring machined T marks, and a mil-spec finish. These uppers are made for us right here in the USA by a mil-spec manufacturer.
